{"lemma": "رَفَثٌ", "slug": "رَفَثٌ", "root": "ر.ف.ث", "root_slug": "ر-ف-ث", "root_link": "/words/roots/ر-ف-ث", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "رَفَث", "root": "رفث", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 2}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n16103"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AB%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "coition; obscene speech", "fa": "جماع؛ سخن زنا", "ur": "جماع؛ بولڈ بات", "tr": "cinsel ilişki; laf", "id": "senggama; ucapan", "bn": "যৌনমিলন; কথা", "es": "coito; habla obscena", "fr": "coït; parole", "de": "Beischlaf; Wort", "ru": "соитие; речь", "zh": "性交；粗俗言语"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n16103", "headword_ar": "رَفَثٌ", "root": "rfv", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", said by some to be a simple subst., but by others to be an inf. n., (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Foul, unseemly, immodest, lewd,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obscene, speech,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in relation to women;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T;) this being the primary signification: (Lth, T:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "talk to women in,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "respecting, coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA:) and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "speaking plainly of what should be indicated allusively, relating to coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "allusion to coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "foul, unseemly, immodest, lewd,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obscene, speech addressed to women;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, Mgh, K;) so accord. to I'Ab: (T, S, Mgh:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "kissing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "amatory and enticing talk,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "conversation;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any other similar act, of such acts as occur in the case of coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) or with the pudendum, (A, Mgh,) or with respect to the pudendum, (Msb,) it is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Mgh, Msb:) and with the tongue, (A, Mgh,) or with respect to the tongue, (Msb,) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making an appointment for coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Mgh, Msb:) and with the eye, (A, Mgh,) or with respect to the eye, (Msb,) the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "making a signal of a desire for coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Mgh, Msb:) or it is a word comprehending"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "everything that a man desires of his wife."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, T.) In the Kur ii. 193, where it is forbidden during pilgrimage, it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, T, Mgh, Msb:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "speech that may be a means of inducing coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, T:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "foul, unseemly, immodest, lewd,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "obscene, speech:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, Mgh, Msb:) or, accord. to Th, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "removal of external impurities of the body, by such actions as the paring of the nails, and plucking out the hair of the armpit, and shaving the pubes, and the like."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M. [In the L and TA, the explanation"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1119}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of Th is so given as to relate, not to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rafavN", "text_ar": "رَفَثٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but, to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA rafava", "text_ar": "لَا رَفَثَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]) And in the same, ii. 183, where it is allowed in the night of fasting, it means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Coition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "going in"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to one's wife; syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ifoDaA='", "text_ar": "اـِفْضَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; wherefore it is made trans. by means of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilaY", "text_ar": "اـِلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ifoDaA='", "text_ar": "اـِفْضَا=ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M, Mgh.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "Lth", "T", "S", "M", "Mgh", "Msb", "K", "A", "Zj"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}